Error: cannot use --output in workspace mode
Each package writes to its customElements path from package.json.
To target a single package, use: cem generate -p packages/foo -o custom-path.json
Usage:
 cem generate [files or glob patterns] [flags]

Flags:
 --demo-discovery-file-glob string Glob pattern for discovering demo files
 --demo-discovery-url-pattern string Go Regexp pattern with named capture groups for generating canonical demo urls
 --demo-discovery-url-template string URL pattern string using {groupName} syntax to interpolate named captures from the URL pattern
 --design-tokens string specifiers (relative paths or npm:@scope/package/path/file.json) to DTCG-format module design tokens
 --design-tokens-prefix string css custom property prefix for design tokens
 -e, --exclude stringArray files or glob patterns to exclude
 -h, --help help for generate
 --no-default-excludes do not exclude files by default (e.g. .d.ts files are included unless excluded explicitly)
 -o, --output string write custom elements manifest to this file
 -w, --watch watch files for changes and regenerate

Global Flags:
 --config string config file (searches .config/cem.{yaml,yml,json,jsonc} then .cem.{yaml,yml,json,jsonc})
 -p, --package string package specifier: npm:@scope/package, URL (https://cdn.example.com/pkg/), or local path
 -q, --quiet quiet output (only warnings and errors)
 --source-control-root-url string Canonical public source control URL corresponding to project root on primary branch. e.g. https://github.com/bennypowers/cem/tree/main/
 -v, --verbose verbose logging output

